width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/01/09/1092140137_0:0:3072:1728_640x0_80_0_0_2a1df99492965284e84b71aa354e6fc7.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/01/09/1092140137_0:0:3072:1728_1280x0_80_0_0_6a7b414437167e638d5009ca90d35751.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/01/09/1092140137_0:0:3072:1728_1920x0_80_0_0_bdb9c50d53d2ba307ede1f0e677c207b.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 美联社照片 / Wilfredo Lee </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据莫斯科（人造卫星）网报道：《华尔街日报》周三援引知情人士的话说，现年 44 岁的佛罗里达州州长罗恩·德桑蒂斯将于下周正式启动他的 2024 年总统竞选活动，因为他的竞选捐助者将开始筹款闪电战。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">德桑蒂斯决定向美国联邦选举委员会提交正式文件，宣布他的候选资格，这与 5 月 25 日在迈阿密举行的捐助者会议相对应，这使州长与另一位共和党总统候选人、前美国总统唐纳德特朗普直接竞争。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">包括前南卡罗来纳州州长尼基黑莉在内的其他几位候选人也在参选，尽管他们在民意调查中远远落后。据传，特朗普的前副总统迈克彭斯也在考虑参选。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>据该报报道，会后将举行更正式的活动，但细节尚未透露。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">德桑蒂斯目前在民意调查中仅次于特朗普，但在他正式宣布后很可能会取得一些进展。去年夏天，德桑蒂斯的势头似乎越来越大，他在一些民意调查中击败了特朗普，并以 4% 的优势赢得了共和党活动家的投票。然而，最近几个月他的支持率有所下降，民意调查聚合网站 FiveThirtyEight 的支持率落后前总统超过 31 个百分点。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>尽管如此，德桑蒂斯仍可能是特朗普获得总统提名前的最大障碍。所有其他传闻或确认的候选人都以个位数进行投票。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">特朗普去年年底宣布了他的 2024 年竞选活动。现任公职人员乔·拜登于 4 月正式启动了他的连任竞选活动。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 18 May 2023 03:50:31 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230518/florida-governor-desantis-to-formally-launch-his-presidential-bid-next-week---reports-1110432329.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230518/florida-governor-desantis-to-formally-launch-his-presidential-bid-next-week---reports-1110432329.html<category>美洲</category><category>罗恩德桑蒂斯</category><category>唐纳德·特朗普</category><category>尼基海莉</category><category>佛罗里达</category><category>共和党</category><category>2024 年美国总统大选</category><category>共和党初选</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[New Evidence May Show Trump Was Warned Mar-a-Lago Docs Were Not Automatically Declassified]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110431663" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/03/16/1108676833_0:0:3072:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_6ecd7a013e78191f84e0d393658b0e74.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1108676674" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230518/new-evidence-may-show-trump-was-warned-mar-a-lago-docs-were-not-automatically-declassified-1110431663.html?share-img=1108676674"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / Lynne Sladky</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">Поместье Дональда Трампа в штате Илорида</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="Поместье Дональда Трампа в штате Флорида  - Sputnik International, 1920, 18.05.2023" title="Поместье Дональда Трампа в штате Илорида" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/03/16/1108676833_0:160:3072:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_cb0ec4d6717c112578868213aa7e3a3e.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/03/16/1108676833_0:160:3072:1888_640x0_80_0_0_1a0ea86443a409ef096c9ac7285f83e1.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/03/16/1108676833_0:160:3072:1888_1280x0_80_0_0_1554383ec29ab7d91a859f16eea6eb65.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/03/16/1108676833_0:160:3072:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_cb0ec4d6717c112578868213aa7e3a3e.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 美联社照片 / Lynne Sladky </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">伊恩德马蒂诺</div><div class="article__author-links"> <a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_demartino_ian/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">去年 8 月，联邦调查局突击搜查了特朗普的海湖庄园，没收了数千份文件，其中包括数十份被标记为机密和绝密的文件。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">美国国家档案馆已通知前总统唐纳德特朗普，它将向特别顾问杰克史密斯移交 16 份记录，这些记录显然表明特朗普及其高级顾问在他任职期间已获悉正确的解密程序。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> <a href="https://www.cnn.com/2023/05/17/politics/trump-letter-archives-special-counsel-declassification/index.html" target="_blank">美国媒体</a>获得了档案保管员黛布拉·施泰德尔·沃尔给特朗普的信，信中写道： </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “有问题的 16 份记录（将被发送给杰克·史密斯）都反映了与亲密总统顾问的沟通，其中一些是针对你个人的，涉及你是否、为什么以及如何解密某些机密记录。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110431663" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230518/new-evidence-may-show-trump-was-warned-mar-a-lago-docs-were-not-automatically-declassified-1110431663.html?share-block=1110431961" data-title="“The 16 records in question [that will be sent to Jack Smith] all reflect communications involving close presidential advisers, some of them directed to you personally, concerning whether, why, and how you should declassify certain classified records.”"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>这些记录于去年被传唤，可能会影响以史密斯为首的大陪审团调查特朗普在 2021 年 1 月离开白宫时是否对机密文件处理不当的调查。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">特朗普坚称，作为总统，当他将文件从白宫带走时，这些文件会自动解密。美国总统有权解密任何文件，但通常要遵循一个程序来这样做。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">特朗普和他的盟友说，他下达了解密材料的<strong>“常规命令”</strong> 。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">信中还指出，特朗普试图通过引用“基于宪法的特权”来阻止史密斯访问这 16 项记录，但沃尔拒绝了这一说法。它指出史密斯的办公室已经表示它准备证明为什么这些记录可能包含<strong>“对大陪审团的调查很重要”的证据。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">信中说，除非法院命令阻止，否则这些文件将于 5 月 24 日移交。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">上周在美国电视台播出的市政厅会议上，特朗普再次表示，总统记录法允许他在离任时带走这些文件。然而，该法案规定，当总统离任时，国家档案馆将成为所有总统记录的合法保管人，这些记录属于公众。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 18 May 2023 03:47:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230518/new-evidence-may-show-trump-was-warned-mar-a-lago-docs-were-not-automatically-declassified-1110431663.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230518/new-evidence-may-show-trump-was-warned-mar-a-lago-docs-were-not-automatically-declassified-1110431663.html<category>美洲</category><category>唐纳德·特朗普</category><category>杰克史密斯</category><category>联邦调查局</category><category>机密文件</category><category>海湖庄园</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[First-Ever State-Wide TikTok Ban Imposed by Montana]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110431282" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/0c/08/1105192525_0:0:3072:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_08821712234a8cb4517dbe27ba2738bd.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1105192508" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230518/first-ever-state-wide-tiktok-ban-imposed-by-montana-1110431282.html?share-img=1105192508"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / Michael Dwyer</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">2022 年 10 月 14 日星期五，在波士顿的手机上可以看到 TikTok 标志。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="The TikTok logo is seen on a cell phone, Friday, Oct. 14, 2022, in Boston. - Sputnik International, 1920, 18.05.2023" title="2022 年 10 月 14 日，星期五，在波士顿的手机上可以看到 TikTok 徽标。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/0c/08/1105192525_0:160:3073:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_0402ee49ad074a5697ed5f421a3a59b7.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/0c/08/1105192525_0:160:3073:1888_640x0_80_0_0_502eb21e4b3cc1124b2c810ebccae57b.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/0c/08/1105192525_0:160:3073:1888_1280x0_80_0_0_dd7c2f3760c3c203d60346535d98d0b1.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/0c/08/1105192525_0:160:3073:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_0402ee49ad074a5697ed5f421a3a59b7.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 美联社照片 / Michael Dwyer </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">伊恩德马蒂诺</div><div class="article__author-links"> <a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_demartino_ian/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">美国的几个州已经禁止政府设备使用社交媒体应用程序，但如果蒙大拿州法律生效，它将是第一个完全禁止该应用程序的州。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">周三，蒙大拿州正式成为第一个通过法律完全禁止该州使用社交媒体应用程序 TikTok 的州。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">在法律措施轻松通过该州共和党控制的立法机构后，州长 Greg Gianforte 于周三签署了该法案。<strong>该禁令定于 2024 年 1 月 1 日生效。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> SB-419 法规定，只要蒙大拿州的用户“可以选择下载 TikTok 移动应用程序”，就会对应用商店和 TikTok 处以 10,000 美元的罚款，并且只要违规行为继续存在，就会继续对它们处以罚款。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> TikTok 发言人布鲁克·奥伯韦特表示，该法律违反了第一修正案，并试图缓解蒙大拿州用户的担忧。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “我们想让蒙大拿人放心，他们可以继续使用 TikTok 来表达自己、谋生和寻找社区，因为我们将继续努力捍卫蒙大拿内外用户的权利，”她说。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110431282" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230518/first-ever-state-wide-tiktok-ban-imposed-by-montana-1110431282.html?share-block=1110431821" data-title="“We want to reassure Montanans that they can continue using TikTok to express themselves, earn a living, and find community as we continue working to defend the rights of our users inside and outside of Montana,” she said."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">立法者和联邦调查局表示，他们担心该应用程序可能会被中国政府用来监视美国公民。 TikTok 已采取多项措施安抚美国官员，但似乎无济于事。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">它已开始将所有美国用户数据转移到美国软件巨头甲骨文拥有的服务器上，将总部迁至新加坡，并一直在推动一项 15 亿美元的计划，以满足美国官方的要求。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="vrez"><div class="article__vrez"><div class="article__vrez-text"><p>该计划名为 Project Texas，将从非 Oracle 运行的服务器中删除所有美国历史用户数据，并创建一个名为 TikTok US Data Security 的独立美国实体，该实体将独立于 TikTok 母公司字节跳动运行。</p><p>此外，该项目将由外部观察员监督。</p></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">尽管如此，一些立法者仍抱怨这还不够，这一说法似乎激怒了 TikTok 总法律顾问埃里希·安德森 (Erich Andersen)。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “我们哪里做不到？”安徒生在接受美国媒体采访时说。 “在某些时候，你会超出网络安全风险评估等范围，然后你就会说‘我们不喜欢你的国籍。’” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110431282" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230518/first-ever-state-wide-tiktok-ban-imposed-by-montana-1110431282.html?share-block=1110431291" data-title="“Where are we falling short here?” Andersen said in an interview with US media. “At some point you get beyond the cybersecurity risk assessment, etcetera, and you get to ‘We don’t like your nationality.’”"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">该法律的反对者表示，除了可能违反第一修正案外，它也很难执行，并指出虚拟专用网络服务 (VPN) 允许用户更改任何设备的地理位置。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">该法案的支持者指出了体育博彩应用程序，这些应用程序使用地理围栏来对抗这种情况，并使用户更难欺骗他们的位置。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">然而，这种方法可能需要 TikTok 的每个合法用户向该应用程序提供更多的个人数据。 GeoComply 等地理围栏公司让用户有责任证明他们不在禁止使用 GeoComply 的应用程序的位置（例如体育博彩和某些金融服务）。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="vrez"><div class="article__vrez"><div class="article__vrez-text"><p> GeoComply 声称服务于“100% 的美国 iGaming 市场” <strong>，其工作原理是更深入地了解用户的移动设备，并要求他们在使用 PC 时下载专有软件。</strong></p><p>它的网站称，它使用“GPS 卫星数据、无线和蜂窝网络数据以及互联网连接”来确定用户位置，同时还“与其他设备信息进行交叉引用，以确定用户是否试图掩盖他们的位置。通过不同方式报告的设备性能、网络性能、内存使用情况和时钟差异。”</p></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">简而言之，这意味着该服务使用移动设备上可用的每个位置数据点。它还会查看设备当前正在运行的应用程序以及设备处理器的工作强度。它使用该数据来确定用户是否可能在后台运行 VPN。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>该要求不适用于蒙大拿州的用户</strong>，他们根本无法合法访问该应用程序。相反，TikTok 必须让全球所有其他用户向他们提供数据，证明他们没有使用 VPN 并且不在蒙大拿州。即使 TikTok 试图将要求限制在美国，蒙大拿州的用户也可以简单地使用 VPN 出现在美国境外。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">其中一些数据点已经被 TikTok 监控，但其他数据点，如 GPS 位置数据，对用户来说是可选的。如果 Geofencing<strong>被用来执行法律，而 TikTok 遵守它，蒙大拿州实际上将迫使全球 16 亿 TikTok 用户（包括超过 1.5 亿美国用户）向该应用程序提供更多数据，以阻止其 110 万居民从访问它。</strong> </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="vrez"><div class="article__vrez"><div class="article__vrez-text"><p>从理论上讲，GeoComply 可能被迫将这些数据与 TikTok 分开，但这将需要用户下载一个单独的应用程序，而且他们的网站上并不清楚他们与客户分享了哪些信息。它确实说它不会向第三方出售信息。</p></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">美国前总统唐纳德特朗普首先试图通过行政命令在美国禁止 TikTok，要求它和基于中国的消息应用程序微信向美国实体出售或被禁止进入该国。该命令被法院搁置，并被现任美国总统乔·拜登撤销。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>然而，近几个月来，拜登披上了禁止 TikTok 的外衣，并同样威胁称，如果中国投资者拒绝出售其在该公司的股份，将禁止它。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">已经提出了几项立法来在全国范围内禁止该应用程序，最突出的是 RESTRICT ACT，该法案得到了两党的支持。该法案在其文本中从未提及 TikTok、字节跳动，甚至“社交媒体”，它将赋予政府广泛的权力来限制远远超出 TikTok 等社交媒体应用程序的服务。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">该法案的措辞是开放式的，但批评人士表示，如果对其进行广泛解读，政府将有权关闭其认为构成威胁的外国公司运营的几乎所有在线服务。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">参议员 Rand Paul (R-KY) 阻止了 RESTRICT 法案在参议院的一致通过。从那以后，它一直在等待在场内进行正式投票；但是，尚不清楚何时或是否会对该法案进行表决。该法案还遭到美国众议员亚历山大·奥卡西奥-科尔特斯 (D-NY) 等年轻民主党议员的反对。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">电子前沿基金会 (EFF) 是一个在线权利和隐私激进组织，也反对限制法案，称蒙大拿州的法律将无法达到其目的，同时也违反了宪法。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “<strong>这项违宪禁令破坏了蒙大拿州 TikTok 用户的言论自由和结社自由，侵犯了 TikTok 传播其用户视频的利益。这公然违反​​了第一修正案，无论是国会还是蒙大拿州，”</strong> EFF 在一系列推文中表示。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “这项禁令不会保护蒙大拿州居民的私人数据。公司将继续收集个人信息并将其货币化，并将其广泛提供给购买者、窃贼和外国演员。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110431282" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230518/first-ever-state-wide-tiktok-ban-imposed-by-montana-1110431282.html?share-block=1110431307" data-title="“This ban won’t protect Montana residents' private data. Companies will continue to harvest and monetize personal info and make it widely available to purchasers, thieves, and foreign actors.”"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> EFF 建议立法者通过数据隐私法，而不是针对 TikTok 的狭隘立法。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p>安徒生表示，TikTok 同意这条道路。他说：“我们的观点是，我们真的会欢迎广泛而平等地适用的基础广泛的立法。” “坦率地说，我们不喜欢的是针对一家公司的立法。” </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110431282" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230518/first-ever-state-wide-tiktok-ban-imposed-by-montana-1110431282.html?share-block=1110431309" data-title="Andersen said TikTok agrees with that path. “Our view is that we would really welcome broad-based legislation that applies broadly and evenly,” he said. “What we don’t like, frankly, is legislation that is sort of targeted at one company.”"></div></div></div></div></div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 18 May 2023 03:41:27 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230518/first-ever-state-wide-tiktok-ban-imposed-by-montana-1110431282.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230518/first-ever-state-wide-tiktok-ban-imposed-by-montana-1110431282.html<category>美洲</category><category>蒙大拿</category><category>甲骨文</category><category>抖音</category><category>格雷格·吉安福特</category><category>互联网审查</category><category>禁止</category><category>中国</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Global Warming to Mark Hottest-Ever Temps, Exceed 1.5-Degree Threshold in Next 5 Years]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110430821" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/107897/86/1078978612_0:0:3063:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_b43b2f1188a67b5ec1927fa589cdbe3a.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1078978610" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230518/global-warming-to-mark-hottest-ever-temps-exceed-15-degree-threshold-in-next-5-years--1110430821.html?share-img=1078978610"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / Branden Camp</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">2017 年 6 月 3 日，星期六，美国最大的二氧化碳排放源之一的燃煤电厂 Scherer 矗立在佐治亚州朱丽叶的远处</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="The coal-fired Plant Scherer, one of the nation's top carbon dioxide emitters, stands in the distance in Juliette, Ga., Saturday, June, 3, 2017 - Sputnik International, 1920, 18.05.2023" title="2017 年 6 月 3 日，星期六，美国最大的二氧化碳排放国之一的燃煤电厂 Scherer 矗立在佐治亚州朱丽叶的远处" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/107897/86/1078978612_0:32:3063:1755_1920x0_80_0_0_c567fc04051ce79bef905a4c75b1606f.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/107897/86/1078978612_0:32:3063:1755_640x0_80_0_0_b3e9b953f057a39549933912401dec40.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/107897/86/1078978612_0:32:3063:1755_1280x0_80_0_0_6cc8a2903db908e5e5089467e31c113b.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/107897/86/1078978612_0:32:3063:1755_1920x0_80_0_0_c567fc04051ce79bef905a4c75b1606f.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © AP Photo / 布兰登坎普</div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">叶戈尔·沙波瓦洛夫</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_shapovalov_egor/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a><a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:e.shapovalov@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">2015年《巴黎协定》为各国制定了减少全球温室气体排放的长期目标，旨在本世纪将全球气温控制在2°C以下，同时努力确保气温不超过1.5°C；然而，新的调查结果表明，这个上限可能很快就会被打破。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">世界气象组织 (WMO) 提交的一份新报告显示，全球地表温度很可能在未来五年创下令人担忧的记录。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>据科学家称，从 2023 年到 2027 年，地球近地表的年平均温度将比工业化前水平高出 1.5 度——《巴黎协定》规定的门槛——至少持续一年。分析师表示，这种情况发生的可能性为 66%。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">与此同时，官员们表示，有 98% 的可能性在 2023 年至 2027 年之间至少有一年，或整个五年期间将记录自有记录以来最热的温度。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">此外，这段时间北欧、西伯利亚、阿拉斯加和非洲萨赫勒地区的降雨量将增加，而亚马逊河和澳大利亚部分地区的降雨量将减少。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> WMO 秘书长佩特里·塔拉斯表示，预测的温度峰值“<strong>将对健康、粮食安全、水资源管理和环境产生深远影响。我们需要做好准备。”</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">自 2015 年以来，温度暂时超过 1.5°C 的概率稳步上升，当时该概率接近于零。 2017 年至 2021 年，超标概率为 10%。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">据世界气象组织称，五年平均值超过 1.5 度的可能性为 32%。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">研究人员将创纪录的高温归因于大气中存在影响全球变暖的温室气体，以及厄尔尼诺现象。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> 2022 年全球平均气温比 1850-1900 年的平均气温高约 1.15°C。另一种现象拉尼娜现象的降温效应暂时抑制了过去三年大部分时间的长期变暖趋势。但拉尼娜现象于 2023 年 3 月结束， <a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230512/noaa-warns-el-nino-arrival-could-mark-significant-event-persist-into-winter-1110276161.html" target="_blank">厄尔尼诺现象预计</a>将在未来几个月内展开。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">除了全球气温升高外，人为温室气体还导致海洋进一步升温和酸化、 <a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230216/doomsday-glacier-rapidly-shedding-ice--we-should-all-be-very-concerned-study-warns-1107505852.html" target="_blank">海冰和冰川融化</a>、海平面上升和更多的极端天气模式。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 18 May 2023 03:11:08 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230518/global-warming-to-mark-hottest-ever-temps-exceed-15-degree-threshold-in-next-5-years--1110430821.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230518/global-warming-to-mark-hottest-ever-temps-exceed-15-degree-threshold-in-next-5-years--1110430821.html<category>超越政治</category><category>世界气象组织 (WMO)</category><category>佩特里·塔拉斯</category><category>拉尼娜现象</category><category>全球暖化</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[UK Carrier Strike Group Will Return to Indo-Pacific in 2025]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110431100" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/07/0d/1083379936_0:0:3068:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_cd9961f377abdfc92f84de86f18dd25b.jpg?source-sid=" data-photoview-image-id="1083379934" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230518/uk-carrier-strike-group-to-return-to-indo-pacific-in-2025-1110431100.html?share-img=1083379934"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© 7 月 12 日，英国航母打击群、罗纳德·里根号航母打击群和硫磺岛两栖战备群<a href="https://www.dvidshub.net/image/6729070/uss-ronald-reagan-cvn-76-underway-operations-with-uk-carrier-strike-group-21" title="西曼·格雷·吉布森">的 Seaman Gray Gibson</a></span><span class="photoview__desc-text">舰艇在亚丁湾编队作战。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="" alt="Ships of the UK Carrier Strike Group, USS Ronald Reagan Carrier Strike Group, and Iwo Jima Amphibious Ready Group operate in formation in the Gulf of Aden, July 12. - Sputnik International, 1920, 18.05.2023" title="7 月 12 日，英国航母打击群、罗纳德里根号航母打击群和硫磺岛两栖战备群的舰艇在亚丁湾编队作战。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/07/0d/1083379936_0:161:3068:1887_1920x0_80_0_0_145efacad6146779d9784580e4b9ddbf.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/07/0d/1083379936_0:161:3068:1887_640x0_80_0_0_a023c323ee7ad342d8ecac7236f8aca2.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/07/0d/1083379936_0:161:3068:1887_1280x0_80_0_0_3583732fc804e91d61b29ccce79b2314.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/07/0d/1083379936_0:161:3068:1887_1920x0_80_0_0_145efacad6146779d9784580e4b9ddbf.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © <a href="https://www.dvidshub.net/image/6729070/uss-ronald-reagan-cvn-76-underway-operations-with-uk-carrier-strike-group-21" title="西曼·格雷·吉布森">海员格雷吉布森</a></div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据莫斯科（人造卫星）网报道：英国政府周三表示，英国航母打击群将于 2025 年返回印太地区——距该航母首次在该地区航行已过去四年。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “英国将于今天 [5 月 18 日] 确认其航母打击群将在 2021 年首次航行到该地区后于 2025 年返回印度太平洋地区，”英国政府在网站上的一份声明中表示。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">英国首相 Rishi Sunak 和他的日本首相 Fumio Kishida 周四在广岛举行会议，将签署一项名为《广岛协议》的新全球战略伙伴关系，包括国防、贸易、投资、科学、技术、解决全球问题等方面的新协议和气候变化，声明中写道。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">根据协议，预计苏纳克还将与东京就新的网络合作伙伴关系达成一致。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">苏纳克在周四访问东京海军基地期间宣布，将在即将举行的第四次英日联合“警戒岛”军事演习中将英国军队人数增加一倍，达到约 170 名现役军人。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> 2021年5月，由伊丽莎白女王级航母率领的英国航母打击群进行了为期28周的航行，期间首次停靠印度、日本、韩国、新加坡等港口。航行期间，该编队参加了与日、美、韩、印等国军队的联合军演。 2021年7月，航母驶过南海。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 18 May 2023 02:38:37 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230518/uk-carrier-strike-group-to-return-to-indo-pacific-in-2025-1110431100.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230518/uk-carrier-strike-group-to-return-to-indo-pacific-in-2025-1110431100.html<category>军队</category><category>英国</category><category>航母打击群</category><category>里士苏纳克</category><category>岸田文雄</category><category>英国</category><category>日本</category><category>印太</category><category>军事部署</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Dramatic Spending Cut Only Way to Avoid Recession But US Won't Commit - Investor]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110430615" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/102692/70/1026927066_0:0:3500:2331_1440x900_80_0_1_37e848fe3c78f1a462d87b295f196223.jpg?source-sid=afp" data-photoview-image-id="1026927065" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230518/dramatic-spending-cut-only-way-to-avoid-recession-but-us-wont-commit---investor-1110430615.html?share-img=1026927065"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / MOHD RASFAN</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">安邦外币交易商</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="afp" alt="A foreign currency dealer in Ampang  - Sputnik International, 1920, 18.05.2023" title="安邦的外币交易商" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/102692/70/1026927066_0:181:3500:2150_1920x0_80_0_0_320a37dea74249e55aaef089856faac8.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/102692/70/1026927066_0:181:3500:2150_640x0_80_0_0_a39e28d2e073ded22b898cbff98d2ccb.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/102692/70/1026927066_0:181:3500:2150_1280x0_80_0_0_771f6b0d22fd79b327965e710f2199d8.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/102692/70/1026927066_0:181:3500:2150_1920x0_80_0_0_320a37dea74249e55aaef089856faac8.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / MOHD RASFAN </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据华盛顿（人造卫星）网报道：美国著名投资者吉姆·罗杰斯告诉人造卫星网：美国摆脱迫在眉睫的衰退的唯一途径是大幅削减开支，但这不是华盛顿准备做的事情。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “出路是什么？这很容易。如果华盛顿说‘好吧，我们将停止支出，我们将偿还债务，’”罗杰斯说。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “现在，你认为华盛顿会停止支出吗？他们喜欢花钱。这不是他们的钱。出路就是大幅削减支出，大幅减税并停止支出。他们会这样做吗？不，当然不是。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110430615" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230518/dramatic-spending-cut-only-way-to-avoid-recession-but-us-wont-commit---investor-1110430615.html?share-block=1110430728" data-title="&quot;Now, do you think Washington is going to stop spending? They love spending money. It's not their money. The way out is just cut spending dramatically, cut taxes dramatically and stop spending. Are they going to do it? No, of course not.&quot; "></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">罗杰斯还谈到了美国印钞问题，强调历史多次表明，当一个国家大量印钞时，就会出现通货膨胀，货币贬值。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “有时货币变得一文不值，”他说。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “国家花了很多钱，债务货币增加，货币变得越来越不值钱，变得一文不值，所以他们给你新的钱。他们告诉你它更值钱，但这仍然是一个问题。这是一个国家衰落。这些都是简单的历史教训。如果你愿意，你可以毁掉你的货币，许多国家已经一再贬值他们的货币。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110430615" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230518/dramatic-spending-cut-only-way-to-avoid-recession-but-us-wont-commit---investor-1110430615.html?share-block=1110430729" data-title="&quot;Countries spend a lot of money, the currency of the debt builds up, the currency becomes less and less valuable, becoming worthless, and so they give you new money. They tell you it's worth more, but it's still a problem. It's a country in decline. These are simple lessons from history. You can ruin your currency if you want and many countries have debased their currency repeatedly.&quot; "></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这位投资者说，通常情况下，该国不会转身复苏，继续作为“二等或三等国家”，因为它的钱不那么值钱。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> 5 月初，美联储主席杰罗姆·鲍威尔 (Jerome Powell) 表示，美国可能会陷入他希望的温和衰退。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">美联储 3 月份的政策会议纪要显示，美联储的政策制定者预计美国将在今年晚些时候经历“温和衰退”，可能需要两年时间才能克服。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 18 May 2023 02:25:59 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230518/dramatic-spending-cut-only-way-to-avoid-recession-but-us-wont-commit---investor-1110430615.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230518/dramatic-spending-cut-only-way-to-avoid-recession-but-us-wont-commit---investor-1110430615.html<category>经济</category><category>支出单</category><category>我们</category><category>吉姆罗杰斯</category><category>杰罗姆·鲍威尔</category><category>华盛顿</category><category>美国联邦储备</category></item></channel></rss>